    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "text": "My father (may God have mercy on him) narrated to us. He said: Ali ibn Ibrahim ibn Hashim narrated to us, from his father, from Ali ibn al-Hakam, from al-Mufaddal ibn Salih, from Jabir, from Abu Ja'far (peace be upon him) who said: When this verse, \"And brought, that Day, is Hell\" [89:23] was revealed, the Messenger of God (may God bless him and his family) was asked about that, so he said: The Trustworthy Spirit informed me that God -- there is no god other than Him -- when He gathers the firsts and the lasts, Hell will be brought, steered by a thousand reins, each rein held by a hundred thousand rough, severe angels. It has a clunk, rage, and a wail. It wails with such a wail that, had God, Mighty and Majestic, not delayed them for the Judgment, it would have consumed everything. Then, a flare will emerge from it that will surround the creatures, both the righteous and the transgressor. God has not created a single servant from His servants, neither an angel nor a prophet, except that he will cry out: \"O Lord, my self, my self!\" But you, O Prophet of God, will call out: \"My Nation, my Nation!\" Then a Path will be placed upon it, thinner than the edge of a sword. Upon it are three arches: the first bears trust and kinship, the second bears prayer, and the third bears the justice of the Lord of the Worlds. They will be made to pass upon it, and trust and kinship will trap them. If they overcome that, prayer will trap them. If they overcome that, the end is with the Lord of the Worlds, and that is His saying: \"Surely, your Lord is in observation\" [89:14]. The people will be upon the Path -- hanging on, a foot slipping, a foot holding firm -- and the angels around them will call out: \"O Forbearing One! Forgive and pardon! By Your grace, give peace!\" And the people will fall into it like moths. If a person is saved by the mercy of God, he will look at it and say: \"Praise be to God who saved me from you after despair, by His favour and His grace. Surely, our Lord is Forgiving, Thankworthy.\"",
        "summary": "Imam al-Baqir (AS) narrates the Prophet's description of the Day of Judgment when Hell will be brought steered by a thousand reins held by fierce angels. A bridge (Sirat) thinner than a sword's edge will be placed over Hell with three checkpoints testing trust/kinship, prayer, and divine justice. The Prophet alone will intercede for his nation while all others cry for themselves.",
        "key_terms": {
          "جهنم": "Jahannam (Hell): the abode of punishment in the afterlife",
          "صراط": "Sirat: the bridge over Hell that all must cross on the Day of Judgment",
          "الروح الأمين": "The Trustworthy Spirit: the angel Jibril (Gabriel)",
          "قناطر": "Arches/bridges: checkpoints on the Sirat"
        },
        "seo_question": "What is the description of the Sirat bridge over Hell on the Day of Judgment in Shia hadith?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "text": "میرے والد نے ہم سے بیان کیا۔ آپ نے فرمایا: جب یہ آیت نازل ہوئی تو رسول اللہ سے پوچھا گیا۔ آپ نے جہنم اور صراط کی تفصیل بیان فرمائی۔",
        "summary": "امام باقر نے قیامت کے دن جہنم اور صراط کی تفصیل بیان فرمائی۔",
